    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-01-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-01-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="168"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2300/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Kingdom of the Serbs, Groats and
                        Slovenes</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-21T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1924—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Your January 18, 7 p.m.<note n="97" xml:id="d168fn97">Not printed.</note>
                    Minister of War has just informed me that he is happy to grant all requests your
                    19, December 22, 3 p.m.,<note n="98" xml:id="d168fn98">See footnote 92, <ref
                            target="#pg_232">p. 232</ref>.</note> and will shortly send me
                    confirmation in writing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
